entries.text: Appearing like a comet, the rough diamond of a star.
It's the cute-cool idol, Hoshimachi Suisei-bui.
I just did a chatting stream recently.
I kinda want to play a game.
But starting a long RPG or something is...
I want to do a long game, but...
I can't stream super frequently right now.
My Live is coming up soon too.
What's something that doesn't use my voice much?
I want to play a "work game."
There isn't really anything trending right now.
Hmm, maybe I should play something from the past.
I just played PlateUp! recently too.
Should I do the Rice Ball shop?
Should I play a card game?
Come to think of it, what happened to Fast Food Simulator?
I've done solo ops so much...
I just remembered something from the past.
Back when this Fast Food Simulator was trending,
Holomembers were playing it a ton together.
But my schedule never worked out, so I couldn't join.
I mastered it all by myself.
As a result of mastering it alone...
I became a human incapable of cooperating with others.
I'm pretty sure that's the history here.
That's how I ended up being a solo operation.
I did play a bit behind the scenes...
They tried to assign roles like "You go here, you do this,"
But because I had become a sad solo-op machine,
Well, I played a little test run just now to enjoy it,
I was just trying to remember what it was like.
I think I'll set the game difficulty to Easy for now.
Just let me play on that.
And since I remembered a bit just now,
I think I'm good to go.
I have to froth the milk.
Just in case, I'll put another milk...
Why are you only using one hand?!
We fry, right? I'll fry the chicken patties for now.
This is... um, I need to pour new oil in.
I have oil. Is this oil enough though?
Ah, it's gone now. So, um, fry the potatoes. Well, I've never worked a part-time job. Not at a fast food place.
Like this... um, I collect it with this, right?
This is prep work. Alright, still good.
And next, I fry the nuggets.
Hum-hum-hum. I've got this part down perfectly.
Did I fill the drinks? Ah, I didn't.
Hoi, hoi, hoi, hoi. Wrong order.
And, um, fill from L. Right is L, middle is M, left is S. Enough?
Okay, enough. And this again... ah, careful. Oh, oh!
I fried them in contaminated oil. Ah, I did it. Ah, I messed up.
So that's bad? Wait, will I get yelled at?
Dammit. I thought it was still okay.
Food loss. "You're streaming a lot lately?" Really? You think?
I don't think it's that much. February is...
Well, this week is mostly... because the Live is coming up,
They aren't putting in that much work for me. Next week might have a bit? No, well, it's about average.
No, there's no oil. I'll fry in this one.
Singer on! 77 is probably getting risky...
I feel like it's still good... wait. I know. With these things, you watch over it for a sec. I feel like it can go.
I feel like I can barely make it with this pollution level.
Let's push the limits. Push the limits.
The Fes prep is incredibly busy.
I can go, still can go, still can go.
Hmm, actually this is bad, actually.
Which one? Which is first? Which is first?
Which one... no, this is actually bad.
"Thanks for streaming even though you're busy."
This year, compared to usual years...
I don't really understand why, but...
I don't know why it turned out like this...
Yeah, that's how it is. That's right.
"You always say that." No, for real!
Alright, next is the meat. Like this.
Maybe it's a problem with the scale of it.
Should I just grill them all?
No, if there's one left, let's grill it.
"Can you take it easy after the Fes and Live are over?"
No, listen, there is no future where I take it easy this year.
A future where I can say "I relaxed a bit" doesn't seem to exist.
Was there always this flipping motion? I wonder.
And I'll make these cheese, right?
I plan to make this a super busy year.
Ei, ei, ei, ei, ei, ei, ei!
Ei! Ah! Wrong! Ah! Shai, shai, shai, shai, shai! Crap, crap, crap, crap!
Ah! Don't grill! Don't grill! Wait, wait! Pick up! Pick up! Pick up first! Pick up! Whatever happens to that one slice, fine! Whatever!
I don't care. Really. Cheese here. Patty here. Normal ones.
Everything's ready, right? Milk is in too.
Should I put it here? The corner.
Here we go. "Watching burgers makes me hungry." I totally get that.
Watching these burgers makes me want to eat one so bad.
What burger do you like? Cheese, maybe? Cheese hamburger?
When I tried it, it was delicious. I was like "This is good!"
And strawberry ice cream later. And...
Strawberry ice cream and potato S.
"Did you try the Kinoko no Yama McFlurry?"
Sui-chan hates sweet things, you know.
If it's spicy, I'll eat it.
I might be a little bored.
And, um, fried potato and strawberry ice cream.
Light Splash Cola and coffee, is it?
Coffee, Light Splash Cola, and Double Chicken Burger.
Mr. Hop. It looked like Fried Potato S.
I thought I'd do this just to remember...
Crap, I haven't cleared the chicken nuggets.
Should I do this one first?
Don't get mad over the amount of ice!
Chicken Burger helps. Chicken isn't selling.
Should I not fry this many? Double Cheese.
1, 2, 3, 4... wait, how many times did I place it? I don't know.
Um, and strawberry ice cream and hamburger.
"I ordered extra coffee but there isn't much coffee."
But I always have this much left over.
Why do I have so much left?
Right, it really depends on the day.
Did I forget to put anything away? No.
Ah, actually I'm kinda running out around here too.
Maybe just one of these is enough.
And, didn't forget to close anything.
Ice cream is sweet, but I can eat it.
I'm happy if it's not sweet.
I'm happy if it's not too sweet.
Easy was a little too easy, so...
Should I go to the main menu?
If it's Matcha, I can do it.
I don't really like tea as tea.
I'd prefer to make them in advance.
Crap, I forgot to put the cheese away.
No, I knew I'd forget to put it away.
4 nuggets is definitely not enough, right?
Today is a Normal day, so maybe...
This is fine for chicken for now.
Did I run out of meat?
Hoi. Let's just grill all of these.
Cheese, cheese, cheese, cheese, cheese, cheese, cheese, cheese...
Actually, I like Sukiya's Cheese Gyudon.
Used as an insult now, though.
I've been mad about this for ages.
Don't use Sukiya's Cheese Gyudon as a slur!
Having nothing to do in between is a bit...
Maybe it's easier if I put it in...
The drive-thru leaves fast, if I recall.
Coffee with extra milk, vanilla ice cream.
Let's just have this guy go home.
Um, start with the easy ones.
Water and Fried Potato is L.
Ah, just serve the chicken nugget.
It looked like strawberry ice cream.
The other one is probably this way.
It looked like strawberry ice cream.
Huh? I'm making something... This didn't launch.
That was kinda close... Didn't go perfectly though.
There's a wrapped burger here... I don't understand anything anymore.
Restock, restock. Anyway, gotta do this.
I want a trash can nearby. Um, and tomatoes.
Tomato. How many people usually play this game? Eh, isn't it like 6 people?
I've only ever played it alone on stream.
It's not that I'm being shunned.
Well, maybe this is just right. With this much leftover...
Nuggets and potatoes... well, well, well, maybe it's just right.
There were a lot that didn't get thrown in.
Throwing stuff around here seems pointless, so don't need to throw it.
Why isn't there a trash can nearby?
I want to add trash cans.
In PlateUp!, I can add them.
Can't I buy a trash can?
Freezer is fine like this for now.
L seems a bit short, but maybe it's fine.
I never bought anything before, but I had to buy stuff like this? I see.
I wondered what this was, but it was for that. It's totally fine, buying from here.
Okay, buying. Gotta buy lots of stuff.
Um, um, what was it? Potato.
Restocking time is, look, chatting time.
Manager wants to go home already.
I wondered when it would end...
Was it 2 and a half hours?
Recently I've been doing 2.5 hours though.
My head was spinning so much.
I'll try not to spoil it, but...
I watched it with my sister.
"Eh, so this means that happened, right?"
Well, just the parts I was curious about.
In short, what does it mean?
The fact that it's Netflix Limited...
They say it's showing in theaters too, but...
"It's easier to understand if you read the novel version."
I like how each chapter is concise.
Is the next one the last one?
I don't know. If "5" comes, it wouldn't be weird if it ends.
"Sui-chan, what did you eat on Meat Day?"
Eh, I don't really know... what was it? I ate meat like "Tomosankaku."
It's not a cut you eat at home.
Well, I didn't eat it at home.
"Sui-chan, do you eat Kalbi or Horumon (offal)?"
I like it, I guess, but...
It's fatty so I can't eat a lot.
Well, Hachinosu (Honeycomb tripe) is a bit fatty.
Marucho (Small Intestine) is good, good but... like that.
"Popularity Minus 100" what? What happened? But it's popular.
Almost time. Ah, I just had to do this.
I just had to do this. Wait, cheese.
This area is mostly OK. Pour in the milk.
Then fry this and the nuggets.
Potatoes, potatoes, potatoes, potatoes, I want to eat them~
When we have dinner parties at my house, almost certainly at the end, potatoes...
I want to run a potato specialty shop.
But it was different from what I was seeking.
In Ginza or somewhere, there's a shop where you can choose the potato type.
I want to go there once.
Most places just let you enjoy the difference in sauces.
Nuggets definitely won't be enough with this.
"There's a fry specialty shop in Ibaraki too."
Among frozen ones, there's like a Crispy Potato type.
What, what, what, what, what, what, what?
And here is Double Hamburger and Light Splash Cola.
Yes, yes, yes, here you go.
Should have been vanilla ice cream.
I thought I should do people without hamburgers first.
And Fried Potato M and water.
Um, Fried Potato L and Nugget M are sold out.
Seems like what you want is a burger.
I put it in? That means...
Cheeseburger, 1, 3... missing so add 1, um, um, 3.
This is fast. Chicken Burger helps!
Um, I don't know which is which anymore.
Coffee is in. 17 is vanilla ice cream.
Um, this is Number 14. Um, L and Double Shot.
Don't get mad! Don't leave, please!
And, coffee with milk. Um, strawberry ice cream and...
"This isn't the size of potato I ordered."
Ah, and trash bags run out.
Seems like there should be more efficient ways.
Right now, solely with my brain capacity...
I'm managing within my brain capacity.
Yeah, I know! I want to optimize like PlateUp!
Wait, can I actually hire staff?
Ah, no, but I'm the one cooking?
Ah, no, I want someone to cook.
I mean, I'm not recruiting or anything.
Like, I'm just expecting it on my own.
Right, just expecting it on my own.
Maybe I'll restock and end for today.
I feel like they'll say that.
Just like how I played Suika Game alone forever.
I fried them, but we had enough.
You guys can go home too.
If I hire them, will they come right now?
No, placing things neatly might be my job? Maybe.
Don't we have ice cream cups?
I changed the chairs but they didn't change!
Have to store things here over there, right?
If I'm here, he loads it, but the place is wrong!
Don't need to put it inside.
I guess this stuff doesn't need to be inside.
But learn by watching for next time.
There won't be a next time.
I hate saying the same thing twice.
Don't make me say the same thing.
Ah, this was a coffee cup.
I've been waking up early and sleeping early.
So I thought I should get used to waking up early now.
Must go home, must go home.
Oh, it turned out like this.
Thought maybe it would be added.
How is this room right now?
It's a bit dirty right now, messing it up, but...
Cleaning it now, wait a sec.
"Waiting at the entrance." You're the kind type.
Almost time for the Live, everyone.
Right, eh, everyone, write text on the fans (uchiwa), big text.
Ah, the venue sales notice went out?
"I like the 'Shoot for the Moon' dance."
Wondering if I should make an Information account.
I leave it to the Hoshiyomis.
Eh, if it fits regulations, it's fine.
There are lots of rules for fans.
"Event where Ute jacks the Holo Shop 'To the Moon' starting."
"I think some have reposted already, but..."
"Regarding venue sales notice, due to price correction..."
"On sale at Hololive Production Official Shop..."
There's a place to buy drinks.
Like, I signed a bunch recently too.
Eh, how many did I sign? I signed a lot, thinking "What is this for?"
"Suisui-san, please sign for the blank-blank collab."
"This is displayed at blank-blank." "Ah, really." (Signing) "What is displayed at blank-blank?"
Like 3... lots. I feel like I signed 60. 60.
What was it... like on T-shirts. Signing away.
"You don't grasp it?" Can't keep up.
Manager-san is working hard. Thanks, Mari-chan.
No, that 60 is... not all for the same thing.
Various separate projects. Probably signed that much.
Maybe like lottery? Presents for winners?
I'm probably the only Holo talent worried about retiring at 60.
Aiming for the 21st, gotta fix body and throat.
"I don't have much work this week," I said...
But this week is almost ending.
Going for walks on days off.
Going to solve mysteries or play...
I want to do that, but...
If I catch a cold, it's over.
Wondering what to do. Staying inside all the time is also...
But catching a cold is bad. Flu is spreading.
Next stream is... when is it?
When is it... lemme check calendar.
Wait, on the 14th there's a collab.
On the 14th, if Miko-san's health recovers, it's a Micomet collab.
Actually, there's something we've been warming up.
I think we can debut it.
Wonder if Mikochi's health is okay.
"Are you taking a break after Birthday again?"
No, maybe no break this year.
Because I forgot to mention it, can't adjust it.
It was the season for long breaks though.
"When are you resting?" Eh, maybe not this year.
Going to be hectic again this year. "Finished Otoshidama project?" Not at all.
Gotta call everyone. Too long. Let's end soon.
"Resting during Golden Week?" Eh, don't know.
Thank you for your hard work, everyone.
Please buy stream tickets and such.
Please check out the goods too.
I want to eat a burger.
I want to eat a potato.
I want to eat a chicken nugget.
I want to eat a fast food.
I want to eat a burger.
